(50, 'document', 'text/html', 'Working Alone, Together', 'Working Alone, Together', '', 'working-alone,-together', '', 1, 0, 0, 47, 0, 'Many independent workers, finding themselves alienated, are joining a new generation of co-working spaces  ', '<p>Information technology heralded the coming of telecommuters and freelancers able to work from their living rooms, untethered from the office cubical. Recently, independent workers have begun seeking an alternative to the isolation of working from home. Co-working spaces in the US have nearly tripled since 2008, now numbering near 800 and some charging USD$10,000+ per month for added amenities. “The design strategy is a typology that looks at accidental encounters as much as organizational encounters, or efficiency.” Tenants see great benefit in the interdisciplinary environment as they seek a fresh take on their projects.</p>', 1, 10, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1367968517, 30, 1372437017, 0, 0, 0, 1368051780, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/articles/working-alone,-together.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(51, 'document', 'text/html', 'Way of the future', 'Way of the future', '', 'way-of-the-future', '', 1, 0, 0, 33, 0, '', '<p>MIT’s Media Lab bills itself as anti-disciplinary, a research environment that “fills the white spaces between disciplines”. Since their inception in 1985, the Lab has produced innovations including the technology behind Kindle’s ink display. Unburdened by the strings of public funding, the Lab is supported by 80 “member ” companies that provide the center most of its USD$35M annual operating budget, supporting 50 visiting scientists and 140 undergraduate students. In exchange for their support, members are able to use whatever technology emerges from the Lab royalty free.</p>', 1, 10, 4, 1, 1, 1, 1367974209, 30, 1372436724, 0, 0, 0, 1368054540, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/articles/way-of-the-future.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
