(76, 'document', 'text/html', 'Expedia Releases Insiders List of Top Hotels', 'Expedia Releases Insiders List of Top Hotels', '', 'expedia-releases-insiders-list-of-top-hotels', '', 1, 0, 0, 5, 0, 'Expedia released its list of the world''s top hotels, showing that value, location and service all earn their place.', '<p>This week Expedia, a user review site with more than 130,000 hotels in its databases, released their <a title="Expedia''s Insider Select List" href="http://www.expedia.ca/p/hotel-deal/insiders-select.htm" target="_blank">Insiders’ Select list</a> of the world’s top hotels. The ranking is based on more than 500,000 guest reviews and expert input.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Here’s a quick look at the top 3.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>One&amp;Only Palmilla Resort</h4>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_One&amp;Only_Room.png" alt="One&amp;Only Room View" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>(San Jose Del Cabo, Mexico)</p>\r\n<p>From $488/night</p>\r\n<p><em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>“The resort’s rooms (173 in total) have all the luxe touches you’d expect — lavish bathrooms, flat-screen televisions, Bose surround sound — plus such surprise extras as telescopes on every balcony for whale-watching by day and stargazing by night. Even the smallest rooms are essentially suites, but it’s the level of service that sets the resort apart. From welcome drinks and a butler (who will unpack your bags for you) to poolside foot massages and aromatherapy turndown service, you’ll feel pampered from arrival to departure.”</em></p>\r\n<p>-<a title="Jetsetter" href="http://www.jetsetter.com/hotels/mexico/los-cabos/2981/one-only-palmilla" target="_blank">Jetsetter</a></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>A long-time celebrity haunt, The One&amp;Only may be the priciest resort in the top three but it is clear that people are willing to part with the extra cash for the superior service and added amenities such as garment pressing and a personal butler to help you settle into your room.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Arenas del Mar Beachfront &amp; Rainforest Resort</h4>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_Arenas-del-Mar_Room.png" alt="Arenas View" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">(Quepos, Costa Rica)</span></p>\r\n<p>From $270/night</p>\r\n<p><em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>“Down-to-earth eco-chic comes standard at this 11-acre rain-forest-and-beach resort with a conscience. A go-to hideaway for adventure-seeking, luxury-loving travelers, Arenas del Mar harmoniously mixes creature comforts with authentic experience, without disturbing its pristine Pacific coast location. The setting is one of the resort’s greatest assets, and each of the 38 rooms and suites has a spectacular view of either the rain forest or one of two white sand beaches on the Pacific.”</em></p>\r\n<p>-<a title="Jetsetter" href="http://www.jetsetter.com/hotels/costa-rica/manuel-antonio-national-park/800/arenas-del-mar-resort?nm=serplist&amp;cl=1&amp;ca=view-more" target="_blank">Jetsetter</a></p>\r\n<p> <span style="line-height: 1.5em;"> </span></p>\r\n<p>Whereas One&amp;Only excel at service, Arenas del Mar’s highlight is the location. They take full advantage of the crashing waves and rain forest atmosphere with expansive wrap-around terraces attached to each room. Arenas exposes you to your natural surroundings and then gently get out of the way, stepping in only to ensure comfort and relaxation. Bird watching, zip-lining, jungle tours and indigenous crafting are all popular activities offered by the hotel.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Marrol’s Boutique Hotel</h4>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_Hotel-Marrols_Exterior.png" alt="Marrol''s Exterior" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p>(Bratislava, Slovakia)</p>\r\n<p>From $180/night</p>\r\n<p><em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>”This luxury boutique hotel, a member of the prestigious Small Luxury Hotels of the World, has only 54 guest rooms and suites. It has all the amenities you''d expect from a 5-star hotel—a superb restaurant, a full spa, luxurious rooms—and an excellent location in the heart of Old Town''s charming cobble-stoned streets. But that''s not the biggest draw, according to Expedia users: it''s the price.”</em></p>\r\n<p>-<a title="Business Insider" href="http://www.businessinsider.com/worlds-best-hotel-according-to-expedia-users-2012-6" target="_blank">Business Insider</a></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Marrol’s was Expedia’s number 1 pick in 2012, a spot it earned with its tremendous value. At $180/night including breakfast, there is plenty cash left over to enjoy the full spa and local attractions. The restaurant, like the hotel itself embraces the local culture; you wont find overplayed modern dining here, only refined old-world cuisine in a traditional setting. Value and cultural rootedness are what make Marrol’s stand out in this years top list.</p>', 1, 11, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1376064190, 1, 1376929700, 0, 0, 0, 1376065620, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/hospitality/expedia-releases-insiders-list-of-top-hotels.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(77, 'document', 'text/html', 'Lanserhof', 'Lanserhof', '', 'lanserhof', '', 1, 0, 0, 92, 0, 'The winner of many prestigious awards, Lanserhof is securing it’s place the world’s best destination spa and expanding its footprint by opening an urban day centre in nearby Hamburg.', '<p><strong>Location:</strong> Innsbruk, Austria<br /><strong>Established:</strong> 1998<br /><strong>Keys:</strong> 90</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recommended Minimum Stay:</strong> 14 days</p>\r\n<p><strong>Single Room (20 sqm):</strong> EUR 210<br /><strong>Apartment (50 sqm):</strong> Unlisted</p>\r\n<p>Room Rates must be accompanied by a Basic Package (see below)</p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Basic Package</strong> (excluding accommodation)<br />(medical exam, massage, analysis, movement therapy, presentations): EUR 1366</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><em>“...health awareness and mindfulness must belong to the requisite know-how of each and every one of us. Enduring and sustainable well-being plays a decisive role in dealing with the routine and daily challenges in life.”</em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Originally functioning as a holiday hotel, Lanserhof was acquired in 1998 by a consortium of investors who redeveloped and modernized Lanserhof into a regenerative holistic health center.The team at Lanserhof is interdisciplinary and focus on creating an individualized approach to healing, recognizing therapeutic intervention is a single component of a “complete philosophy of health” . The Lans Med Concept is based on the FX Mayr philosophy, focusing on the health of the gut, aiming to “improve ones health through digestive detoxification.”</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img title="Lanserhof Bath" src="assets/research%20assets/wellness/images/130823_Hamburg-Bath.png" alt="Lanserhof Bath" width="620" height="826" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Each program begins with an initial medical examination and consultation, followed by targeted massage and detox programs and concludes with a progress analysis and recommendation.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Lanserhof has racked up numerous awards winning the European Health and Spa Awards “Best Medical Spa” for four consecutive years and the World Spa Awards “Best European Destination Spa.”</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>In 2012 Lanserhof opened an urban day center in Hamburg to administer four weekly Mayr therapy. The 1,500 square meter facility “provides space for the most modern medicine, purposeful methods of treatment and worthwhile moments of regeneration”</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img title="Lanserhof Hamburg Hallway" src="assets/research%20assets/wellness/images/130823_Hamburg-Hallway.png" alt="Lanserhof Hamburg Hallway" width="620" height="826" /></p>', 1, 11, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1377549211, 1, 1385397815, 0, 0, 0, 1377550860, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/lanserhof.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(78, 'document', 'text/html', 'Biotonus', 'Biotonus', 'Biotunus focuses on “diseases of civilization”, aiming to serve as a refuge for the overworked and burnt-out. ', 'biotonus', '', 1, 0, 0, 92, 0, 'Biotunus focuses on “diseases of civilization”, aiming to serve as a refuge for the overworked and burnt-out. ', '<p><strong>Location:</strong> <span>Montreux, Switzerland</span><br /><strong>Established:</strong> 1983<br /><strong>Keys:</strong> 110</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Stay:</strong> 7 days</p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Packages:</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Weight Reduction: USD$10,500 </p>\r\n<p class="p1">Stress Reduction: USD$10,500 </p>\r\n<p class="p1">Revitalization:  USD$18,000 - 20,000</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p class="p1"><em>“more life to years, not more years to life”</em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Biotonus Clinique Bon Port is integrated into the Grand Hotel Excelsior in Montreux. The clinic focuses heavily on what they term “diseases of civilization”, including stress, burn-out, diabetes, cardiovascular diseases, obesity and diabetes, insomnia.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>All treatments begin with a full analysis of 100 parameters through blood, stools and urine analyses, conventional radiology, cardiovascular tests, morphological-nutritional analysis, and ultrasound scans. Programs are then tailored to the specific results of each individual. A core aspect of their treatment is addressing the use of psychoactive drugs and create personalized plans to eliminate their use in their patients.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img title="Biotonus Breakfast" src="assets/research%20assets/wellness/images/130826_Breakfast.png" alt="Biotonus Breakfast" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Biotonus has become a popular destination for the nearly 60,000 affluent Chinese medical tourists, China Daily reported last year. Europe is a popular destination, estimated to attract 75% of travelers.</p>', 1, 11, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1377550930, 1, 1385145061, 0, 0, 0, 1377551580, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/biotonus.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(79, 'document', 'text/html', 'La Reserve Geneva Hotel & Spa', 'La Reserve Geneva Hotel & Spa', 'La Reserva was recently awarded best anti-aging spa and is not only a destination for travellers, but also serves a healthy local market. ', 'la-reserve-geneva-hotel-and-spa', '', 1, 0, 0, 92, 0, 'La Reserva was recently awarded best anti-aging spa and is not only a destination for travellers, but also serves a healthy local market. ', '<p><strong>Location:</strong> <span>Bellevue, Switzerland</span><br /><strong>Established:</strong> 1969<br /><strong>Keys:</strong> 102</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Stay:</strong> 7 days</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rooms: </strong>USD$500</p>\r\n<p><strong>Suites: </strong>USD$1,600</p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Packages: </strong><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">4-day Better Aging, excluding accommodation: USD$3,500</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>La Reserva located on a 10 acre park overlooking lake Geneva, features a 2,000 sqm wellness center focusing on three key areas: “healthy age management, nutritional consultation and deep relaxation.” The wellness center features 17 treatment rooms, an indoor pool, fitness center, hair salon, sauna and health bar.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img title="Spa-Pool" src="assets/research%20assets/130826_Spa-Pool.png" alt="Spa-Pool" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>La Reserva is located 10 minutes from the city center and has become popular with both local families and destination. A Gondola water taxi ferries guests to and from town for day trips between spa treatments. Conde Nast recently voted La Reserva the “Best Anti-Aging Spa” noting its non-invasive weight loss program and service that eliminates all guest concerns except simply showing up.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Three on-site restaurants feature cuisine ranging from ultra-simple local produce and hand-made pastas to a traditional Chinese menu served in opulent surroundings.</p>', 1, 11, 4, 1, 1, 1, 1377552423, 1, 1385145107, 0, 0, 0, 1377551580, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/la-reserve-geneva-hotel-and-spa.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(80, 'document', 'text/html', 'Clinique La Prairie', 'Clinique La Prairie', 'Clinique La Prairie is arguably the World’s most exclusive medi-spa specialising in anti-aging with cutting edge technology and a dedicated product R&D program.', 'clinique-la-prairie', '', 1, 0, 0, 92, 0, 'Clinique La Prairie is arguably the World’s most exclusive medi-spa specialising in anti-aging with cutting edge technology and a dedicated product R&D program.', '<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Location:</strong> Clerens<span>, Switzerland</span><br /><strong>Established:</strong> 1931<br /><strong>Rooms: </strong>17</p>\r\n<p><strong>Junior Suites: </strong>6</p>\r\n<p><strong>Suite: </strong>1</p>\r\n<p><strong>Minimum Stay:</strong> 6-13 days</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Packages:</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Standard room (25sqm) + Revitalization Program USD$24,000</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Suite (181sqm) + Revitalization Program USD$32,000</p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">Perched above Lake Leman, looking out upon the Alpine peaks, sits Clinique La Prairie, regarded as one of the most exclusive medi-spa location in the world. La Prairie has been administrating its signature Lamb foetus treatment (now lamb liver) to Royals, celebs and even the Pope. The treatment, first introduced in the 1930s is supposed to help stimulate cellular revitalization, and with a 70% customer return rate, it’s difficult to argue the success. </p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">Billed as a “launch-pad to a brand-new life”, La Prairie is a one-stop-shop, offering basic medical checkups, both general and plastic surgery, a range of specialists, physical therapies and radiology and medical imaging. Programs start at $24,000 for a 6 night stay and top out at just over $50,000 for a 13 night stay, accommodation included. </p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">The spa offers everything from noninvasive skin treatments and weight management to plastic surgery, orthopaedics, gynaecology, dentistry and thalassotherapy, and also has a variety of à la carte programmes and treatments.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p2"><img title="Massage" src="assets/research%20assets/wellness/images/130826_Massage.png" alt="Massage" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">Restrictive diet plans are not advocated at Clinique La Prairie:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1"><em>“Eating or following a diet shouldn’t be a pressure, it should be enjoyed. The key factors are to eat seasonal ingredients, a variety of colors, a good balance of protein, carbs and fat, and not to overeat – you should never feel full or uncomfortable after a meal.”</em></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><em> </em></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><em><img title="Restaurant" src="assets/research%20assets/wellness/images/130826_Restaurant.png" alt="Restaurant" width="620" height="348" /></em></p>', 1, 11, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1377553187, 1, 1385410303, 0, 0, 0, 1377551580, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/clinique-la-prairie.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(81, 'document', 'text/html', 'La Pura Resort', 'La Pura Resort', 'La Pura is an exclusively female resort, centering their care around research into gender specific treatments for all stages of a woman’s life.', 'la-pura-resort', '', 1, 0, 0, 92, 0, 'La Pura is an exclusively female resort, centering their care around research into gender specific treatments for all stages of a woman’s life.', '<p><strong>Location:</strong> Gars am Kamp, Austria<br /><strong>Rooms: 83</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Standard Rooms (24-33 sqm): </strong>USD$191</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Junior Suites (37-47sqm): </strong>USD$230</p>\r\n<p class="p1"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Packages:</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">FX Mayr Program USD$2,000</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Basic Spa Program USD$470</p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1"><em>“The feelgood resort exclusively for women”</em></p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">La Pura features a 1,900sqm Spa that support programs including weight management, pregnancy health management, post-surgery facial repair, and detoxification. All programs at La Pura are designed specifically with women in mind and tailored to their specific medical and aesthetic needs. This concept of gender-specific treatments are at the core of La Pura’s philosophy, seeking to address the needs of women at different stages in their lives: puberty, pregnancy, breast feeding, menopause and old age. </p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p2"><img title="Bathhouse" src="assets/research%20assets/130826_Rassul.png" alt="Bathhouse" width="620" height="348" /></p>\r\n<p class="p2"> </p>\r\n<p class="p1">The nutrition concept is based around easily digested food for a peaceful sleep, and follows the common, local, organic, seasonal mantra. </p>', 1, 11, 3, 1, 1, 1, 1377553713, 1, 1385145093, 0, 0, 0, 1377551580, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/la-pura-resort.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(82, 'document', 'text/html', 'Eastern Promise', '', 'Chinese designers gain recognition as some of the freshest voices in their industries', 'eastern-promise', '', 1, 0, 0, 33, 0, 'Chinese designers gain recognition as some of the freshest voices in their industries', '<p><em><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style="color: #000000;">“<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;">There’s a growing audience for Chinese brands – it’s more lifestyle and homeware products at the moment, but that could change.”</span></span></em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>China''s emerging design stars are gaining the attention of global brands and global markets. Designer Xiao Li recently received the Diesel Award for her runway show in </span></span></span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;">Trieste, Italy and </span></span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span> Hermès and designer Jiang Qiong are opening up </span></span></span><a title="China Daily" href="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2012-02/08/content_14562024.htm" target="_blank">a flagship store in Paris this fall</a><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span> under the Shang Xia brand. All indicative of a shift in perception of Chinese products as well as a commercial recognition that Chinese brands can compete with European brands on an international stage.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span> </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><img title="Xiao Li" src="assets/research%20assets/design/images/130830_Double_Xiao-Li.png" alt="Xiao Li" width="620" height="467" /></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;">“<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>The reputation for cheap production was driven by demand from western brands wanting lower-priced goods but China has a long history of craftsmanship and creating high quality, luxury products.”</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span> </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>Jiang Qiong, as much philosopher as she is designer dismisses the term luxury as a marketing gimmick. “The true luxuries of today are time and emotion.” </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span><span> </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span><span><img title="Jiang Qiong" src="assets/research%20assets/design/images/130830_Portrait-Two_Jiang-Qiong.png" alt="Jiang Qiong" width="620" height="450" /><span> </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span><span> </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span><span>Read more of her interview on The <a title="The Brander" href="http://www.thebrander.com/article.php?o=555" target="_blank">Brander</a></span></span></span></span><span style="line-height: 1.5em;"> </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>See more from Xiao Li''s RCA collection at </span></span></span><a title="Dezeen" href="http://www.dezeen.com/2013/06/05/rca-fashion-2013-collection-by-xiao-li/" target="_blank">Dezeen</a><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>.</span></span></span></p>', 1, 10, 3, 1, 1, 1, 1377892518, 1, 1377895343, 0, 0, 0, 1377892800, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/design/eastern-promise.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(83, 'document', 'text/html', 'Profile: Yves Behar', 'Profile: Yves Behar', 'Yves behar sees designers taking a central role as business recognizes the value in their user-centered approach ', 'profile-yves-behar', '', 1, 0, 0, 33, 0, 'Yves behar sees designers taking a central role as business recognizes the value in their user-centered approach ', '<p><em><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style="color: #000000;">“<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;">We have to be creative with the business model, not just the design side of things.”</span></span></em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Yves Behar<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>, the Swiss born designer and entrepreneur, is an advocate for user centered design. Through his collaborations as designer and brand developer, he has seen that business benefits from “a particular type of thinking that designers can be well suited for: being in the shoes of your customer.”</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>In 2011, the Conde Nast Innovation and Design Awards recognized him as <a title="Conde Nast Traveller" href="http://www.cntraveller.com/magazine/innovation-and-design/2011-ida-winners/designer-of-the-year" target="_blank">Designer of the Year</a>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>Yves sees a “bigger role for design in the future, and the opportunity for designers to be true participants in both for profit businesses, but also non-profit important causes.” His <a title="One Laptop Per Child" href="http://one.laptop.org/about/mission" target="_blank">One Laptop Per Child project</a> is transforming education for some of the world''s poorest children. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>See his presentation on “Holistic Making” below, and read more about his firm <a title="Fuse Project" href="http://www.fuseproject.com/index.php" target="_blank">Fuseproject</a>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/34047962" frameborder="0" width="600" height="450"></iframe></p>', 1, 10, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1377893364, 1, 1377952910, 0, 0, 0, 1377892800, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/design/profile-yves-behar.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(84, 'document', 'text/html', 'Architecture: breaking the mould', 'Architecture: breaking the mould', 'Michael Hansmeyer is pioneering the next frontier in architecture – printable buildings', 'architecture-breaking-the-mould', '', 1, 0, 0, 33, 0, 'Michael Hansmeyer is pioneering the next frontier in architecture – printable buildings', '<p><em><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style="color: #000000;">“<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;">expand your scope of what is possible and what is imaginable – and in the best case create something that is, as yet, unimaginable.”</span></span></em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span><a title="michael-hansmeyer" href="http://www.michael-hansmeyer.com/" target="_blank">Michael Hansmeyer</a> and his colleague Benjamin Dillenburger have built a 20m2 room. More accurately, the architects, based at the Computer-aided Architectural Design Department at the Swiss Federal Institute (ETH) in Zurich have <em>printed</em> a room. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>Using millions of grains of sand bound with a resin and a 3D printer, they have formed a new sandstone compound that can be “woven like fabric.” The result is their modern interpretation of a a grotto, currently on display at the <a title="FRAC center" href="http://www.frac-centre.fr/_en/archilab-492.html" target="_blank">FRAC center</a> in Orleans, France.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;">“<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>The appeal to us is twofold. First, to show the potential of this fabrication technology for an actual building element rather than just a small-scale model. Second, to question traditional notions of materiality.”</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><span>See Hansmeyer present his ideas at TED.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><iframe src="http://embed.ted.com/talks/michael_hansmeyer_building_unimaginable_shapes.html" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="640" height="360"></iframe></p>', 1, 10, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1377894698, 1, 1377952931, 0, 0, 0, 1377892800, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/design/architecture-breaking-the-mould.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(85, 'document', 'text/html', 'REST', 'REST', 'TCM doctor & spa consultant Ken Rosen explains how we busy beings can balance our yin and yang with more rest', 'rest', '', 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 'TCM doctor & spa consultant Ken Rosen explains how we busy beings can balance our yin and yang with more rest', '<p style="color: #000000;"><span lang="en-US"> </span></p>\r\n<p style="color: #000000;"><span lang="en-US">American Ken Rosen has lived in Thailand for almost ten years. A leading </span><a title="TCM" href="http://www.livingoctaveresearch.us/research-categories/wellness/traditional-chinese-medicine.html"><span lang="en-US">Traditional Chinese Medicine</span></a><span lang="en-US"> (TCM) doctor, Rosen works clinically and as a spa consultant at luxury resorts around Asia including Chiva-Som, Six Senses, and Mandarin Oriental. His personal childhood battle with cancer led him to seek alternative health modalities, focusing on the five tenets of TCM: lifestyle, nutrition, acupuncture, herbal medicine, and massage. Rosen believes that our world has a “yin deficiency,” and in this article “Rest” he explains why it is so important to make time for real quiet and calm in the midst of our hectic schedules. Rosen offers practical advice like keeping your sleeping area uncluttered - no books or electronics - and doing 15 minutes of muscle tightening and relaxing exercises.</span></p>\r\n<p style="color: #000000;"> </p>\r\n<p style="color: #000000;">FURTHER READING</p>\r\n<p style="color: #000000;"><span lang="en-US"><a title="Ken Rosen" href="http://www.spatcm.com/" target="_blank">Ken Rosen’s personal webpage</a></span></p>', 1, 10, 3, 1, 1, 30, 1377895463, 1, 1377954020, 0, 0, 0, 1377896400, 30, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'web', 1, 'research-categories/wellness/rest.html', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
